---
/**
 * Static privacy notice for the public website and channel-aware intake flows.
 *
 * The document describes repository-evidenced processing only. It must be
 * reviewed before publication and whenever analytics, marketing, payment,
 * account, client-portal, or attachment-upload features materially change.
 */
import LegalPageShell from "../../components/content/LegalPageShell.astro";
import {
  GENERAL_CONTACT_EMAIL,
  PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL,
  PROJECT_CONTACT_EMAIL,
  SUPPORT_CONTACT_EMAIL,
} from "../../data/contact-channels";

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = "14 July 2026";
const toc = [
  { id: "scope", label: "Who this notice covers" },
  { id: "information", label: "Information we handle" },
  { id: "use", label: "Why we use it" },
  { id: "local-storage", label: "Your browser and PWA" },
  { id: "sharing", label: "Providers and transfers" },
  { id: "retention", label: "Retention" },
  { id: "security", label: "Security" },
  { id: "rights", label: "Your choices and rights" },
  { id: "children", label: "Children" },
  { id: "changes", label: "Changes and contact" },
] as const;
---

<LegalPageShell
  title="Privacy notice"
  description="How Ken Arhin Labs handles general enquiries, support requests, project briefs, necessary technical data, and public PWA storage."
  documentCode="PRV-01"
  documentLabel="Privacy"
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
  summary="This notice explains what information the Ken Arhin Labs public website and communication channels handle, why it is needed, where it is stored, and how to ask questions or exercise applicable privacy rights."
  reviewNote="Obtain qualified legal review before treating this implementation draft as final. Review it again before adding analytics, marketing, payments, accounts, a client portal, or public attachment uploads."
  toc={toc}
  visualStages={["Visit the site", "Share information", "Use your rights"]}
>
  <h2 id="scope" tabindex="-1">1. Who this notice covers</h2>
  <p>
    This notice applies when you visit <strong>kenarhinlabs.com</strong>, use its public
    progressive web app features, send a general enquiry or support request through the{" "}
    <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>, send a project brief through{" "}
    <a href="/start-a-project">Start a Project</a>, or email one of the public addresses described
    below. Privacy, rights, security, and policy requests should be sent to{" "}
    <a href={`mailto:${PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Ken Arhin Labs is the business responsible for deciding how information submitted through
    these public channels is used. The site is intended for a global audience, and additional
    mandatory rights may apply depending on where you live.
  </p>

  <h2 id="information" tabindex="-1">2. Information we handle</h2>
  <h3>Information you choose to provide</h3>
  <p>Every public message form asks for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>your name;</li>
    <li>your email address;</li>
    <li>the subject of your message;</li>
    <li>the message and context you choose to include; and</li>
    <li>a short-lived Cloudflare Turnstile verification token.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The Contact page also records whether you chose General or Support. Support may include an
    optional client or project reference. Start a Project may include an organisation, planning
    range, timeframe, and up to eight selected service areas. Project briefs create a project lead;
    General and Support messages do not. A browser-supplied support reference is not treated as
    proof that you own or may access a client account.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you contact us by email, the information includes your email address, message content,
    routing and message metadata, and any attachments you choose to send. Please do not send
    passwords, payment-card details, health information, government identifiers, production
    credentials, or other sensitive information through a public form or an initial email.
  </p>

  <h3>Limited technical information</h3>
  <p>
    When a form request reaches the public API, it receives a request reference and processes the
    connecting IP address and a shortened browser user-agent string for rate limiting, security,
    abuse prevention, and diagnostics. Cloudflare Turnstile processes browser and network signals
    to issue a verification token. The API sends that token, the expected form action, and where
    available the connecting IP address to Cloudflare for server-side verification before the
    message is accepted.
  </p>
  <p>
    Accepted form submissions are stored as inbox threads and messages in Supabase Postgres. A
    project brief also creates a CRM lead. Confirmation email work is queued after the same durable
    transaction, but form acceptance does not claim that an email has reached its destination. The
    website does not currently provide customer accounts, accept payments, or intentionally run
    advertising or marketing analytics.
  </p>

  <h2 id="use" tabindex="-1">3. Why we use information</h2>
  <p>We use the information described above only as needed to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>read, route, assess, and respond to a general enquiry, support request, or project brief;</li>
    <li>take requested steps toward a possible proposal or client engagement;</li>
    <li>operate, secure, troubleshoot, and prevent abuse of the website and public API;</li>
    <li>maintain correspondence and project records where a relationship develops; and</li>
    <li>meet legal, regulatory, accounting, or dispute-resolution obligations where applicable.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Depending on the context and applicable law, this processing may be based on your request or
    consent, steps toward a possible contract, legitimate operational and security interests, or a
    legal obligation. The contact form does not enrol you in a marketing list.
  </p>

  <h2 id="local-storage" tabindex="-1">4. Your browser and the public PWA</h2>
  <p>
    The site stores the value <code>light</code>, <code>dark</code>, or <code>system</code> under the
    browser key <code>labs-theme</code> so your visual preference can be applied on later visits.
    You can change the preference through the theme control or remove it by clearing this site's
    browser storage.
  </p>
  <p>
    If your browser supports service workers, the public PWA may keep copies of visited public
    pages, fonts, images, and core interface files in browser-managed cache storage. This supports
    faster repeat visits and limited offline use. It does not make contact submissions available
    offline and does not intentionally cache API, authentication, or private account responses.
    You can remove these copies through your browser's site-data or installed-app controls.
  </p>
  <p>
    The current public site does not set an application cookie for analytics, advertising, or
    authentication. Infrastructure or future features must not be treated as covered by this
    statement without a new review and notice update.
  </p>

  <h2 id="sharing" tabindex="-1">5. Providers, disclosures, and international handling</h2>
  <p>
    The public website, API, Turnstile challenge, Email Routing, and transactional email delivery
    use Cloudflare infrastructure. Cloudflare processes the request and challenge information
    needed to route, secure, validate, and deliver those services. More information about
    Turnstile signal processing is available in Cloudflare's{" "}
    <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/en-au/turnstile-privacy-policy/" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Turnstile Privacy Addendum
    </a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Communication threads, messages, workflow state, project leads, and attachment metadata are
    stored in Supabase Postgres. Attachments received by direct email are stored in a private
    Cloudflare R2 bucket and are available only through an authenticated administration route. Raw
    email source is not intentionally stored. The public website forms do not currently accept
    file uploads.
  </p>
  <p>
    We may also disclose information where required by law, necessary to protect people or the
    service, or required to establish or defend legal claims. We do not describe a provider as a
    recipient until the repository and operating process show that it actually handles this public
    data.
  </p>
  <p>
    Internet and cloud providers may process information in more than one country. Where this
    occurs, the intended approach is to use appropriate provider terms, security controls, and any
    transfer safeguards required by applicable law. This statement is not a claim that visitor
    information remains in one country.
  </p>
  <p>
    Links to X, Instagram, LinkedIn, and WhatsApp take you to services operated by those companies.
    Their privacy terms apply after you follow those links; Ken Arhin Labs does not control their
    platforms.
  </p>

  <h2 id="retention" tabindex="-1">6. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to keep personal information only for as long as it is reasonably needed for the
    purpose described in this notice, an active or reasonably anticipated project relationship,
    security and dispute handling, or a legal requirement. No fixed contact-retention period has
    been approved, so this draft does not invent one.
  </p>
  <p>
    When information is no longer needed and no lawful reason requires it to be retained, it should
    be securely deleted or de-identified. Browser theme and PWA cache data remain under your
    browser's storage controls and may also be removed by browser eviction or application updates.
  </p>

  <h2 id="security" tabindex="-1">7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use proportionate technical and organisational safeguards appropriate to a public website,
    including HTTPS in production, input validation, Cloudflare Turnstile, request-rate controls,
    restricted service boundaries, private attachment storage, authenticated administration
    routes, and cache rules that keep message submissions and private inbox data out of public
    runtime caches. No online service can promise absolute security.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you believe information sent through the site has been misused or exposed, contact us at{" "}
    <a href={`mailto:${PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>{" "}with enough detail to
    investigate, but do not include additional sensitive information in the first message.
  </p>

  <h2 id="rights" tabindex="-1">8. Your choices and rights</h2>
  <p>
    Subject to applicable law and reasonable identity verification, you may ask whether we hold
    personal information about you and request access, correction, deletion, or an end to certain
    processing. A request may be limited where another person's rights, confidentiality, legal
    duties, or a lawful retention requirement applies.
  </p>
  <p>
    Send requests to <a href={`mailto:${PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>. We will
    respond within the period and in the manner required by applicable law. Where applicable, you
    may also raise a concern with the data-protection or privacy regulator available where you
    live.
  </p>

  <h2 id="children" tabindex="-1">9. Children and sensitive information</h2>
  <p>
    This business site and its project-enquiry form are not designed for children, and Ken Arhin
    Labs does not knowingly seek personal information from a child through the form. If you are not
    legally able to make an enquiry independently where you live, ask a parent or guardian to
    contact us. A parent or guardian who believes a child supplied information can request review
    or deletion using the email above.
  </p>

  <h2 id="changes" tabindex="-1">10. Changes and contact</h2>
  <p>
    We may revise this notice when the site's features, providers, data flows, or legal obligations
    change. The last-updated date identifies the current draft. Material changes should be made
    visible before the affected processing begins where practical.
  </p>
  <p>
    Privacy questions, corrections, and rights requests can be sent to{" "}
    <a href={`mailto:${PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{PRIVACY_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>. Ordinary business
    enquiries use <a href={`mailto:${GENERAL_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{GENERAL_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>, existing
    project support uses <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>,
    and new project briefs use <a href={`mailto:${PROJECT_CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{PROJECT_CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
    or the <a href="/start-a-project">Start-a-Project page</a>.
  </p>
</LegalPageShell>
